cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.CL 

This paper focuses on fine-grained image classification and image retrieval, which are both related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves a multi-task learning framework and label structures, which are optimization and modeling techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions similarity constraints and embedding, which are techniques used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of shared attributes, which is a topic in natural language processing (cs.CL) and can be applied to image classification.
